ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> prohibits</a> someone involved in a =E2=80=9Cdis=
tribution=E2=80=9D of shares from <em>buying</em> those shares during the d=
istribution. Because the Grayscale Bitcoin Trust is constantly =E2=80=9Cdis=
tributing=E2=80=9D shares, in the sense that anyone could go to them tomorr=
ow with Bitcoins and get back new shares (even though no one has done that =
in two years), Grayscale doesn=E2=80=99t want to also=C2=A0<em>redeem=C2=A0=
</em>shares, because that could be a Regulation M violation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know if that analysis is right=
, but I will say that in 2016 the SEC did <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/30759013.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F=
0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMTYvMzQtNzgyODIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB82ac987b" it=
