<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Indications of interest</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The trading business at an investment bank con=
sists largely of matching up customers who want to buy securities with cust=
omers who want to sell those securities. One way to do that is to sit by th=
e phone waiting for customers to call: If the customers want to sell, you b=
uy, if they=C2=A0want to buy, you sell, and over time you=E2=80=99ll end up=
 moving securities from customers who don=E2=80=99t want them to customers =
who do. But most of the time you are rewarded for showing a bit more hustle=
 than that. If you call a customer=C2=A0and say =E2=80=9Chey, anything you =
want to buy and/or sell,=E2=80=9D she might say yes, and then you have half=
 a trade and just have to find the other half.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course she might say no, and then you don=
=E2=80=99t have a trade. A slightly more compelling approach might be to ca=
ll up the customer and say =E2=80=9Chey, I know you have a bunch of XYZ sto=
ck, and I have another customer who wants to buy it, are you interested?=E2=
=80=9D She could still say no, but you have planted the seed, in her mind, =
that she should do the trade. Also you have suggested that=C2=A0<em>you are=
 the best bank to do it</em>, because you have another customer who wants t=
o buy it. If she does decide to sell the XYZ stock, she might assume that c=
old-calling some=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>bank will get her a worse price (=
because they don=E2=80=99t want it), while calling you back will get her a =
good price (because you already have an enthusiastic buyer lined up).=C2=A0=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ideally you=C2=A0<em>would=C2=A0</em>have the =
buyer lined up =E2=80=94=C2=A0ideally you would be telling the truth =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0but =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean =E2=80=A6=C2=A0it has probably happened,=
 once or twice, in the history of financial markets, that a bank trader has=
 deceived a customer. That he has called up the customer and said =E2=80=9C=
hey I just got a call from=C2=A0another customer who really wants to buy yo=
ur XYZ stock, any chance you are selling,=E2=80=9D when he had not in fact =
gotten such a call. You call one customer saying =E2=80=9Chey I have a moti=
vated buyer for your XYZ stock,=E2=80=9D you call another customer saying =
=E2=80=9Chey I have a motivated seller of XYZ stock and I know you were thi=
nking about it,=E2=80=9D you call some other customers about PQR stock, you=
 work the phones, you=C2=A0rub sticks together until you get a spark, that =
is the job.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course you are also very tidy-minded, effic=
ient and high-achieving so you probably keep a spreadsheet somewhere to tra=
ck=C2=A0all the lies you told customers and generate new ones? This is not =
legal, trading, professional or any other sort of advice, but <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30759013.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMDYvaGstYmFucy1leC1jaXRpLW=
dsb2JhbC1tYXJrZXRzLWJhbmtlci1mcm9tLWluZHVzdHJ5LWZvci0xMC15ZWFycz9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQwMzA3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMDcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB705393b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> here we are</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hong Kong=E2=80=99s Securities and Futures Com=
mission has banned a former Citigroup Inc. banker from re-entering the indu=
stry for 10 years for regulatory breaches, one of the most high-profile dis=
ciplinary actions in recent years.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The financial watchdog said that breaches and =
internal control failures at Citigroup Global Markets Asia Ltd. were attrib=
utable to Philip John Shaw=E2=80=99s inability to discharge his duties as a=
 responsible officer and senior manager, according to a statement on Monday=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The disciplinary action follows the SFC=E2=80=
=99s earlier sanctions against the bank unit for allowing various trading d=
esks under its cash equities business to disseminate mislabeled indications=
 of interest.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/30759013.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly9hcHBzLnNmYy5oay9lZGlzdHJpYnV0=
aW9uV2ViL2dhdGV3YXkvRU4vbmV3cy1hbmQtYW5ub3VuY2VtZW50cy9uZXdzL2RvYz9yZWZObz0=
yM1BSMTI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB798d2d7a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the SFC=E2=80=99s anno=
uncement</a>, and the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/30759013.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly9hcHBzLnNmYy5oay9lZGlzdHJpYnV0aW9uV2ViL2dhdGV=
3YXkvRU4vbmV3cy1hbmQtYW5ub3VuY2VtZW50cy9uZXdzL2RvYz9yZWZObz0yM1BSMTI/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cC798d2d7a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> statement of disciplinary action</a>.=
 From the statement (=E2=80=9CIOI=E2=80=9D stands for =E2=80=9Cindication o=
f interest=E2=80=9D; =E2=80=9CHT Desk=E2=80=9D is the High Touch Equity Sal=
es Trading Desk; =E2=80=9CCGMAL=E2=80=9D is Citigroup Global Markets Asia L=
td.):</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Since at least 2008, the HT Desk had sent IOIs=
 tagged as =E2=80=9CNatural=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9CIn Touch With=E2=80=9D and /=
 or =E2=80=9CP:1=E2=80=9D to clients when there was no genuine client inter=
est or specific client that CGMAL was in touch with (Mislabelled IOIs).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Mislabelled IOIs were generated with refer=
ence to certain percentage of the average daily volumes of selected blue-ch=
ip stocks in the market. The purpose was to provoke client enquiries with a=
 purported belief that traders would be able to find natural opposite flows=
 to cross with the client order given the active trading of the stocks and =
the size of CGMAL=E2=80=99s trading platform. The Facilitation Desk would s=
tep in to provide liquidity when traders failed to source natural liquidity=
 upon client enquiry.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2015, Shaw introduced an Excel spreadsheet =
with built-in macros to allow bulk generation and uploading of Mislabelled =
IOIs by reference to the top 30 or 40 most actively traded stocks in the ma=
rket on the previous day (Spreadsheet). The list of Mislabelled IOIs would =
be shown to the then head of the Facilitation Desk for agreement before the=
y were posted. This practice of using the Spreadsheet to generate and disse=
minate Mislabelled IOIs lasted until December 2018.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Contemporaneous correspondence reveals that Sh=
aw referred to the =E2=80=9CIn Touch With=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CP:1=E2=80=
=9D IOIs generated using the Spreadsheet as =E2=80=9Cfake flow=E2=80=9D and=
 =E2=80=9Cthe fakes=E2=80=9D, indicating that he did not genuinely believe =
that they were correctly labelled.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A number of clients had complained about the q=
uality and accuracy of CGMAL=E2=80=99s IOIs, emphasised the importance of l=
abelling IOIs correctly, and / or pointed out that it was unacceptable for =
CGMAL to advertise facilitation flow using =E2=80=9CIn Touch With=E2=80=9D =
IOIs. Although these complaints were either made to Shaw or brought to his =
attention, he did not stop the dissemination of Mislabelled IOIs.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Note the point that the fake indications =E2=
=80=9Cwould be shown to the head of the Facilitation Desk for agreement bef=
ore they were posted=E2=80=9D: If Citi called a customer and said =E2=80=9C=
hey we think we have someone who wants to buy your XYZ stock,=E2=80=9D and =
the customer said =E2=80=9Csure let=E2=80=99s sell it,=E2=80=9D Citi would =
scurry to find an actual buyer, but sometimes they wouldn=E2=80=99t be able=
 to. At that point, rather than go back to the customer and say =E2=80=9Cwh=
oops we were wrong, no buyer,=E2=80=9D Citi would have to buy the stock its=
elf: =E2=80=9CThe Facilitation Desk would step in to provide liquidity when=
 traders failed to source natural liquidity upon client enquiry.=E2=80=9D S=
o Shaw had to=C2=A0make sure that the Facilitation Desk was actually willin=
g to buy the stock, before he went out and pretended that someone else was.=
</p>
