<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk is the majority shareholder of Twitt=
er Inc. and, as far as I can tell, its acting chief executive officer. He k=
eeps firing everyone at the company who doesn=E2=80=99t do what he wants, a=
nd <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30759013.257411=
/aHR0cHM6Ly9mb3J0dW5lLmNvbS8yMDIzLzAyLzI3L2VzdGhlci1jcmF3Zm9yZC1zYWNrZWQtdH=
dpdHRlci1leGVjLWRlZmVuZHMtZ29pbmctYWxsLWluLWZvci1lbG9uLW11c2sv/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBaa3239f0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> most of the people who do</a>. He keeps mod=
ifying its algorithm to make his own tweets more prominent. I think it is s=
afe to say that he controls Twitter. And yet. If you work at Twitter, and y=
ou see him go into the bathroom, and you barricade him in the bathroom and =
don=E2=80=99t let him out, does that mean that=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>contr=
ol Twitter? Probably not? But he=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/30759013.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGFpbHliZWFzdC=
5jb20vYm9keWd1YXJkcy1mb2xsb3ctZWxvbi1tdXNrLWV2ZXJ5d2hlcmUtYXQtdHdpdHRlci1oc=
S1ldmVuLXRvLXJlc3Ryb29tLXNheXMtZW5naW5lZXI_cmVmPWhvbWU/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB0d7e51b3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> not taking any chances</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Billionaire Elon Musk is routinely=
 followed around Twitter headquarters by two =E2=80=9Cbulky=E2=80=9D bodygu=
ards=E2=80=94even when he goes to the restroom, according to a Twitter engi=
neer. The two bearded guards went viral back in January after they accompan=
ied Musk at a securities fraud trial, and appear to have accompanied him to=
 Twitter after his $44 billion purchase of the social media site. A Twitter=
 engineer identified only as Sam told BBC News: =E2=80=9CWherever he goes i=
n the office, there are at least two bodyguards=E2=80=94very bulky, tall, H=
ollywood movie bodyguards. Even when [he goes] to the restroom.=E2=80=9D He=
 said the constant use of bodyguards suggested that Musk, who has sacked a =
huge number of Twitter staff including coders, does not trust his remaining=
 staff at Twitter HQ in San Francisco.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have to say, nobody makes being a billionair=
e look less fun than Elon Musk. He is the richest person in the world! He d=
ecided to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30759013=
.257411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQ=
tMDQvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWJvdWdodC1zb21lLXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwNzIzX01PTkVZU1=
